    {
      "id": 199669,
      "category": "team",
      "content": "The researcher reported that a Sony endpoint was vulnerable to Local File Inclusion (LFI) and Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF) vulnerabilities. The researcher used the LFI vulnerability to read sensitive files such as /etc/passwd from the web server. The researcher also demonstrated using the SSRF vulnerability to view EC2 instance metadata, and to retrieve an externally hosted .svg file to execute a reflected Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) attack.",
